d 2016","meanings":["English: (i) ethnic name, usually from Old French  <i>Bret</i>, nominative of  <i>Breton</i> ‘Breton’. (ii) ethnic name from Middle English  <i>Brit</i>,  <i>Bret</i>,  <i>Brut</i> (Old English  <i>Brit</i>,  <i>Bret</i>,  <i>Bryt</i>) ‘a Briton’, applied to the Strathclyde Britons up till the 13th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Bret","meanings":["French: ethnic name for a Breton, from Old French <i>bret</i>, nominative of <i>breton</i> ‘Breton’ (see   Breton  ). See also English   Brett  ."]},{"name":"Britto","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Manuel, Alvaro, Dominga, Eufemia, Fermino, Josue, Juana, Pedro, Romulo, Serafin.","Portuguese: variant of   Brito  . This surname is also found in western India, where it was taken by Portuguese colonists.","English: ethnic name from medieval Latin <i>Brito</i> ‘Briton or Breton’, translating Norman French <i>(Le) Bret</i> (compare   Brett  )."]},{"name":"Bratt","meanings":["English (West Midlands): from Middle English <i>brat</i> ‘cloak of coarse cloth’ (Old English <i>bratt</i>), possibly denoting a maker or habitual wearer of such garments. Alternatively, perhaps a variant of   Brett  .","Swedish and Norwegian: from the Old Norse personal name <i>Brattr</i> meaning ‘majestic, proud’ (also, of places, ‘steep’). See also   Bradt  ."]},{"name":"Breton","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Normand, Renald, Adelard, Alphonse, Armand, Gaetan, Laurent, Serge, Adrien, Aime.","French, Breton (mainly Finistère), and English (of Norman origin): ethnic name for a Breton, from Old French <i>breton</i>, oblique case of <i>bret</i> (see   Bret  ). Compare   Lebreton  , see also English   Brett  .","History: In North America, this surname was originally also a secondary surname or <i>dit</i> (‘also called’) name, borne by Jean Élie/Hélie <i>dit</i> (Le) Breton from Ménéac in Morbihan, Brittany (France), who married Jeanne Labbé in Sainte-Famille, Île d'Orléans, QC, in 1669. His descendants also bear the surname   Elie  ."]},{"name":"Britts","meanings":["Probably an Americanized form of German   Britz  .","English: variant of   Britt   (see   Brett  ), with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Britt","meanings":["English: ethnic name for a Celtic-speaking Briton or a Breton, from Middle English <i>brit</i>, <i>bret</i>, Old French <i>bret</i> (see   Brett  ).","German: from a vernacular form of the personal name <i>Brixius</i> (see   Brice  )."]}]},{"name":"Catharina","type":"FIRST","meanings":["English: An English form of Catharine."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Catharina Brett was born about 1132, in France. She married Edmund de Cotentin before 1155. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1132–":"umbes 1132–Surnud","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1132–Female":"1132–Surnud","1189":"1189","before 1155":"enne 1155","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","about 1132":"umbes 1132","1171":"1171","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1132–":"noin 1132–Kuollut","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1132–Female":"1132–Kuollut","1189":"1189","before 1155":"ennen vuotta 1155","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","about 1132":"noin 1132","1171":"1171","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1132–":"environ 1132–Décédée","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1132–Female":"1132–Décédée","1189":"1189","before 1155":"avant 1155","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","about 1132":"environ 1132","1171":"1171","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Catharina Brett est née environ 1132, à France. Elle a épousé Edmund de Cotentin avant 1155. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1132–":"um 1132–Verstorben","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1132–Female":"1132–Verstorben","1189":"1189","before 1155":"vor 1155","1132":"11